Village grocer in Maidensford and a witness in the trial against Elinor Carlisle.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressCaptain Wyatt's Indian manservant.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryThe ‘American Soap King’, supposed richest man in the world<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourCharwoman living in Broadhinny who worked for several local families.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadAda Beatrice Mason is Ruth Kettering's maid and travels with her on the Blue Train.<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainOperative for Special Branch working undercover as a gardener at Meadowbank.<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsLynn’s Mother and younger sister of George Cloade<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodDaughter-in-law of Conway, Frank Conway's widow, Peter's mother.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibrarySecond and much younger wife of Rex Fortescue.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeMaid in the Symmington household in Lymstock, previously employed at Little Furze.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerMaid to dentist Henry Morley in Queen Charlotte Street.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeChinese valet and servant to Mr Paynter.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourSister of Owen Griffith, active in village organisations and committees in Lymstock.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerWest African student resident at Hickory Road who provides an important lead in Poirot's investigation.<br><br>Appears in: Hickory Dickory DockCanadian explorer, naturalist and big-game hunter whose last words spark Bobby Jones's investigation.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansFamous analyst who gives expert evidence at Elinor Carlisle's trial.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressA boy that works in South Adley Mansions and helps the Beresfords.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryA labourer who spotted the glow from the car fire.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibrarySteward on the Paris-to-Croydon flight who is interviewed by Poirot after Madame Giselle's death.<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsGladys Martin's boyfriend, using a false name.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyePolice constable in Broadhinny who assists Superintendent Spence during the investigation.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadFormer gardener at Tudor Cottage and witness to John Savage's will.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansNuclear physicist staying at Mill Cottage with his wife during the fete at Nassecombe.<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyDiffident traveling stockings salesman with epilepsy and memory blackouts; receives anonymous typed instructions and is found near each alphabet murder scene<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersArt collector<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralFormer second footman at Chimneys, later working at the Seven Dials night club.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryMorley’s page boy who announces patient arrivals and lets them up<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeMuch younger second husband of Emily Inglethorp at Styles Court.<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesRose grower called as a witness at Elinor Carlisle's trial.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressSimeon’s eldest son, married to Lydia, lives with Simeon<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasYounger of two sons whom Miss Marple used as an example, he now resides in 'Fairways Mental Home'.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideChief Constable<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en Partya former maid of Miss Marple.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryElderly German-born tobacconist who keeps a small shop in Andover.<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersSecret wife of Prince Ali Yusuf<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsDeceased wife of Patrick Redfern<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunGwenda's Aunt who brought her up in New Zealand.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderAn acquaintance of Miss Marple who is used as an example in a conversation.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Si