esident of 63 Wilbraham Crescent and retired professor<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksAgent working for the Colonel who uses the aliases Nadina and Mrs de Castina.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitTeenage sister of Joyce Reynolds and one of the local girls at the Halloween party.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyNew secretary to Miss Bulstrode at Meadowbank School for Girls.<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsMember of the cleaning staff at Rutherford Hall.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonDaughter of the famous archaeologist Professor Beddingfield (deceased).<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitLongtime member of Dr Leidner's archaeology team in Iraq.<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaYoung woman and guest of Mr Shaitana<br><br>Appears in: Cards On The TableDaughter of Madame Giselle who was brought up in Quebec and later worked as a maid.<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsYounger sister of Clotilde Bradbury-Scott and Lavinia Glynne, living at the Old Manor House in Jocelyn St Mary.<br><br>Appears in: NemesisAdventurous man only just returned to England after 14 years, he accepts the memoirs from James McGrath and helps Virginia Revel.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysSon of Jeremy and Frances Cloade.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodDazzling, carefree young man who loves speed; once ran over two children while driving fast and showed no remorse as he arrives among the invited guests<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneNaturalised Italian-American automobile salesman from Chicago and former chauffeur in the Armstrong household.<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressAcquaintance of Colonel Luscombe who is mistaken for Canon Pennyfather at Bertram's Hotel.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelThe clergyman who was due to marry Verity and Michael and a friend of Miss Temple.<br><br>Appears in: NemesisFriend of Canon Pennyfather who reports him missing.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelMiss Marple’