irginia.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of Chimneys, The Seven Dials MysteryTed Ramsay, young son of Mrs Ramsay and schoolfriend of Geraldine Brown.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksMrs Emma Bishop, housekeeper at Hunterbury, the home of Mrs Laura Welman.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressMiss Blake, one of the younger teachers at Meadowbank School for Girls.<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsInvestigator for the murder at Nasse House<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyPrince Ali Yusuf’s friend and pilot – brother of Joan Sutcliffe, Jennifer’s Uncle<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsFox Terrier belonging to Emily Arundell<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessParisian Scientist<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourValet for Prince Michael, a big brutish man.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysMember of Kramenin's gang who moves in Mrs Vandemeyer's circle.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryEmployee of the Compagnie Wagon-Lis<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressCapable, no-nonsense trained nurse acting as companion to Miss Van Schuyler; handles her employer’s tantrums with calm efficiency aboard the Nile cruise<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileOverbearing matriarch of the Boynton family.<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathBest friend of Elvira from their school in Italy, living with her mother at Onslow Square.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelResident of Wychwood under Ashe, often described as witch-like in appearance.<br><br>Appears in: Murder is EasyInspector Brill, police investigator in the Sad Cypress case.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressManager at Arthur Hasting’s ranch in Argentina<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourFormer RAF pilot married to the late Edith Crackenthorpe; devoted father of young Alexander and still close to Emma, he visits Rutherford Hall frequently<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonSuccessful film actor who had recently been in love with Jane Wilkinson.<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesDr Roger Bryant, passenger on the flight to Croydon and a keen amateur flautist.<br><br>Appears in: Death In The Cloudsthe Ravenscrofts cleaner<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberSecretary to Dr Roberts and one of the supporting figures around the Cards on the Table case.<br><br>Appears in: Cards On The TableAdoptive mother of Desmond Burton-Cox who questions Ariadne Oliver about Celia Ravenscroft's family history.<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberElderly family solicitor who defended Caroline Crale; keeps the trial papers and later directs Poirot to witness statements preserved for sixteen years<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsClergyman and scholar in ancient languages and the Dead Sea Scrolls who goes missing.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelHusband of Mildred Strete, dead before Miss Marple arrives at Stonygates.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsEquerry for Prince Michael, employed by the royal household.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysLong time friend and companion of Poirot, perhaps his only close friendOwner of Sittaford House who lets it to the Willets and moves to Hazelmoor in Exhampton.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryAlias used by the jewel thief King Victor while living in Paris.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysLean, animal-like adventurer and former soldier of fortune; once abandoned twenty East African men to save himself and carries a revolver to the island<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneResident of Sittaford and retired military man.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryLord Carbury, a senior British official encountered by Poirot in Appointment with Death.<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathItalian acquaintance of Lucia Amory and a guest at Abbot's Cleve.<br><br>Appears in: Black CoffeeYoung photographer at the dig from Chicago<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaOnly child of Caroline and Amyas, raised in Canada under a new name; returns at twenty-one determined to clear her mother and asks Poirot to reopen the case<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsAmerican actress and impersonator<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesRetired industrialist and noted collector of Chinese art living in Churston; receives a warning letter and is struck down while caring for his invalid wife<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersLord Edgware’s housekeeper<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesStepdaughter of Mrs Boynton.<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathSpinster sister of Sir Claud Amory who runs his household at Abbot's Cleve and acts as hostess to guests.<br><br>Appears in: Black CoffeeWife of Ameas, accused of his murder, mother of Carla<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsBustling American grandmother traveling to see her daughter; loud, friendly and quick to share anxious chatter with fellow passengers<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressLongtime friend of Emily Arundell and one of the oldest residents of Market Basing.<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessSharp-tongued spinster sister of Dr James Sheppard; runs a “secret service” of maids and milkmen that keeps her abreast of every whisper in King’s Abbot<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydLocal French policeman who assists Poirot at St. Raphaël; gathers statements from railway staff after the Blue Train murder<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainMarried to Lewis Serrecold, sister of Ruth Van Rydock.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsHelper at the party<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyUncompromising, principled governess engaged to watch Angela Warren; notices household tensions, disapproves of Amyas’s infidelity, and guards her charge<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsWidowed sister-in-lar to Roger and Flora’s mother<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydEmployee at the Antique shop where Lucy Eyelesbarrow works.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonDispenser at local hospital (St Catherine’s)<br><br>Appears in: Hickory Dickory DockAriadne Oliver’s godchild and daughter of Alistair and Margaret Ravenscroft.<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberTeacher – founder of Meadowbank with Ms Bulstrode<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsNephew of Emily Arundell, brother of Theresa<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessFamous stage actor and friend of Poirot<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyTamplin’s current younger husband<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainGaunt young man with a Canadian accent who turns up at Fernly Park to see Miss Russell.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydSolicitor and cousin of Nick Buckley<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HouseShop assistant in Woodleigh Common.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyFrail, bedridden wife of Sir Carmichael Clarke; cared for devotedly in their Churston home and central to his reasons for keeping to routine<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersChief Constable of the county where St Mary Mead is located.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the Library, The Murder at the VicarageInspector Dermot Craddock of Scotland Yard and a recurring Miss Marple ally.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From Paddington, The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideInvestigating officer – retired<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberScotland Yard detective who links the missing-person case with a series of large-scale robberies.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelSon of Carrie Louise's first husband.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsMarried to Patrick Redfern, on holiday<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunMarried to ……and passenger on the plane where the murder was committed<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsMystery writer and passenger on the plane where the murder was committed<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsMaid to Mrs Price-Ridley; listens at doors and passes on gossip that feeds village suspicions after the vicar’s study shooting<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageScientist and inventor at Abbotts Cleve.<br><br>Appears in: Black CoffeeActor and master of disguise