 the jewels vanish<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainPoliceman<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyPolice constable in Exhampton who helps discover Captain Trevelyan's body.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryDiligent village constable assisting Inspector Slack; gathers statements around St Mary Mead after the shooting at the vicarage<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicaragePoliceman.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysGreek physician from the Stamboul University Medical Faculty traveling in another coach; examines Ratchett’s wounds and fixes the probable time of death<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressWealthy man staying at the Majestic Hotel in Danemouth.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryYoungest sister of Richard Abernethie, a widow, amateur painter and heiress.<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralPleasant, plain-speaking American cousin and companion to Miss Van Schuyler; her good nature wins friends among the passengers despite her penniless status<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileOfficial in the Hungarian embassy and friend of Gerald Wade.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryTall, courteous Hungarian diplomat married to Helena Goldenberg; travels under his title on the Calais coach and fiercely shields his young wife<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressIn the service of the Colonel.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitThe writer of the memoirs, now deceased.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysHelena Goldenberg Andrenyi, delicate younger sister of Sonia Armstrong, traveling as the Countess with a bruised arm and cherished by her husband<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressHungarian countess and guest at Wyvern Abbey.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryEccentric Russian countess and jewel thief who crosses paths with Hercule Poirot more than once.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourPatient of John Christow suffering with Ridgway’s disease<br><br>Appears in: The HollowButler to the Carpenters who took a telephone message from Mrs Upward for Eve Carpenter.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadCapable, methodical Chief Inspector from Scotland Yard; teams with Japp and Poirot on the alphabet killings, weighing facts with dry skepticism<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersNervy, overworked curate to Reverend Clement; collapses during the inquiry, burdened by guilt over pilfered church funds<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicaragePoirot’s new valet<br><br>Appears in: CurtainDressmaker and wife of captain Dacres<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyOrphaned ward of the Cavendish family; works as a VAD dispenser at the Red Cross hospital and shares the household at Styles during Emily Inglethorp’s poisoning<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesYoung child Vera Claythorne was once governess to who drowned.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneNew York private detective travelling under cover as a typewriter ribbon salesman.<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressOld sea captain, gambler and guest at Sir Charles’ party, married to Cynthia<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyThe young daughter of Lord Caterham, sister to Bundle and Dulcie.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysYoung daughter of Colonel John and Sonia Armstrong.<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressColonel Toby’s wife and Mistress of Styles<br><br>Appears in: CurtainMan whose document Jane Finn is entrusted with.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryEmma Crackenthorpe’s nephew, works at an art gallery.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonA student and relative of Sir Henry and Lady Lucy<br><br>Appears in: The HollowArtist who is seeing Norma Restarick<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlYoung American in his second year with the dig<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaBrother of Rosaleen Cloade and a strong influence over her affairs after Gordon Cloade's death.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodSimeon’s younger son and artist<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasInspector Davis of the King’s Abbot constabulary, first policeman on the scene at Fernly Park and quickly overshadowed when the Cranchester men arrive<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydPatient at Dr Strange’s sanatorium.<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyAbe Ryland’s valet<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourAffable Greek antiques dealer in Paris who knows the jewel trade; offers Poirot insight into the vanished rubies and introduces his shrewd daughter<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainYoung man courting Ann Shapland and later engaged to her.<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsAnother maid at the Ville Genervive and Leonie’s sister<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksCheerful nephew staying with the Clements; provides alibis and comic relief yet inadvertently distracts during key moments of the investigation<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageRuth’s husband, future Lord Leconbury<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainMember of British Intelligence connected with the Meadowbank investigation.<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsPrime Minister of France<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourYoung man in love with Celia Ravenscroft and determined to uncover the truth about her family past.<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberHelp at the party<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyExplorer and Hunter, guest of Mr Shaitana<br><br>Appears in: Cards On The TableDetective Chief Inspector of Scotland Yard and one of Hercule Poirot's oldest police associates.Policeman working on the case.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeInvestigator for the murder at Meadowbank<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsDetective Inspector from county headquarters who takes over the Dillmouth investigation from Inspector Last.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderDetective Inspector in charge of the Wilbraham Crescent investigation in Crowdean.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksEdith and Roger Weatherby’s daughter<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadBasil Blake’s wife, an actress.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryJudge presiding over the trial of the murder of Mrs McGinty<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadMiss Marple's friend, owner of Gossington Hall.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideSerious, protective fiancé of Betty Barnard; struggles between jealousy of her flirting and grief after her seaside strangling<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersSon of Mr and Mrs MacKenzie who died in the war.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeYoung actor and close friend of Bryan Martin in London theatre society.<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesDevoted childhood friend and companion to Letitia Blacklock; frail, fluttery, and thrilled by the odd notice that leads to the staged hold‑up at Little Paddocks<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedDorcas, loyal parlourmaid at Styles Court; gives Poirot key observations about cocoa, draughts, and household quarrels on the night of the poisoning<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesHousemaid employed at The Hollow during the Angkatells' house party.<br><br>Appears in: The HollowDorothea "Dolly" Jarrow, twin sister of Margaret Ravenscroft.<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberThe doctor who inspects the body.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysHead doctor at the Pinewood Private Sanatorium where Helen MacKenzie is a resident.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeFashionable Harley Street nerve specialist; once operated drunk on patient Louisa Clees with fatal results, invited to the island under pretense of a consultation<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneRex Fortescue's doctor.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeThe family doctor for the Reynolds<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyManager of the nursing home in Bournemouth.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryDoctor in St. Mary Mead who knows Katherine Grey and speaks up for Mrs Harfield's sound mind after her death.<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainPhysician living in St Mary Mead and a recurring ally of Miss Marple.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderA doctor from Bethnal Green who attends Rex Fortescue with his doctor Edwin, when Rex falls ill.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeOlder half brother of Helen, a retired doctor.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderCanadian doctor who owns the Grange sanatorium near Merroway Court.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansWorked at the Sanatorium with Dr Haydock.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderDr Quimper, family physician to the Crackenthorpes; discreet, seemingly trustworthy, and closely involved with the household after the body is found<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonPhysician in Marchbolt and Bobby Jones's golfing partner.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansDoctor in Exhampton who helps discover Captain Trevelyan's body.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryPsychiatrist, and Lewis' brother.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsDoctor in Lymstock who had been in practice there for five years at the time of the novel.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerStage performer and twin sister of Bella<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksThe young daughter of Lord Caterham, sister of Bundle and Daisy.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysLocal physician in Merlinville who assists the authorities in the Renauld case.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksAn agent for the 'Comrades of the Red Hand'.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysAlias used by Leo Cayman.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansEldest Crackenthorpe daughter, dead before the story opens; her widower Bryan Eastley and son Alexander remain tied to the family fortunes<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonResident of Broadhinny who had Mrs McGinty as her cleaner<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadAspiring playwright and nephew lodging with his mother at Chipping Cleghorn; sharp-eyed observer of the strange gathering announced in the Gazette<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedClerk at the Mayhew solicitor’s firm<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsVillage shop assistant in Boadhinny<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadYoung typist at the Cavendish Secretarial and Typewriting Bureau in Crowdean.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksDistant cousin to Sir Henry and owner of Ainswick<br><br>Appears in: The HollowReserved English valet to Ratchett; served as Colonel Armstrong’s batman in the war and later his loyal manservant in the New York household<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressWitness from New Zealand who gives evidence about the identity of Mary Gerrard's family.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressPrivate secretary to Sir Claud Amory at Abbot's Cleve.<br><br>Appears in: Black CoffeeYoung man tried for murder; condemned to death after Justice Wargrave’s summing up, though doubts about his guilt later surface among the guests<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneTeenage son of Dr Tanios and Bella Tanios, visiting his grandparents in Market Basing.<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessCounsel for the defence of Elinor Carlisle<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressHousmaid at Gordon Cloade’s London house who survived the bombing<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodEnglish Mistress at Meadowbank<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsYoungest daughter of Rex in love with Gerald Wright.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeMother of Gerald, Robert and Walter Fane, living in Dillmouth.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderTeacher – deputy to Ms Bulstrode<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsMrs Welman’s niece who is accused of murdering Mary<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressTeacher at The Elms school in Woodleigh Common and colleague of Janet White.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyDeceased wife of Bob Gerrard and once lady’s maid to Mrs Welman<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressLavinia’s maid.<br><br>Appears in: NemesisJamaican law student living at Hickory Road and working on her Inner Temple exams.<br><br>Appears in: Hickory Dickory DockTall, dark housekeeper at Fernly Park; Miss Russell guards her privacy, consults Dr Sheppard about “a friend’s” drug habit, and hides a past that links her to Charles Kent<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydFlirtatious young waitress at the Ginger Cat in Bexhill.<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersMarina Gregg's personal assistant.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to Side<b>Disambiguation:</b><br>• <a href="bword://Ellen (Dumb Witness)">Ellen (Dumb Witness)</a> - Member of Emily Arundell’s household staff<br>• <a href="bword://Ellen Wilson">Ellen Wilson</a> - Housekeeper at End HouseMember of Emily Arundell’s household staff<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessHousemaid at Yewtree Lodge.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeHousekeeper at End House, where she has served the Buckley family for many years.<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HouseFenella 'Ellie' Rogers, a rich American oil heiress who marries Mike Rogers.<br><br>Appears in: Endless Night<b>Disambiguation:</b><br>• <a href="bword://Ellis (Jane Wilkinson’s maid)">Ellis (Jane Wilkinson’s maid)</a> - Jane Wilkinson’s maid<br>• <a href="bword://Ellis (Bartholomew Strange’s butler)">Ellis (Bartholomew Strange’s butler)</a> - Butler at Bartholomew Strange’s dinnerButler at Bartholomew Strange’s dinner<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyJane Wilkinson’s maid<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesEloise Renauld, elegant wife of Paul; found bound and gagged on the bed, she is devoted to her son Jack and haunted by her husband’s shadowy past<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksScientist and first wife of Thomas Betterton.<br><br>Appears in: Destination UnknownBeautiful young model sitting for Amyas’s portrait; flaunts her affair with him, later marries into the peerage as Lady Dittisham, but remains marked by the case<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsParlour maid to Mrs Craddock (patient of Dr Roberts)<br><br>Appears in: Cards On The TableMiss Marple’s friend, witness to the murder on the train.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonSister of Superintendent Spence, living in a cottage near Woodleigh Common.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyYoung heiress staying at Bertram’s Hotel.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelRex's first wife, mother of Lance, Percival and Elaine.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeElderly wealthy woman who lives at Littlegreen House with her dog Bob.<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessResident who suffered from an anonymous letter.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerAthletic spinster on holiday at the Jolly Roger Hotel who enjoys rowing and other outdoor pursuits.<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunStern, deeply religious spinster of good family; discharged Beatrice Taylor for immorality and refuses any sense of guilt about the girl’s drowning<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneWealthy matriarch of Styles Court and wife of Alfred Inglethorp.<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesYoung model investing the murder to prove her fiance innocent.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryMiss Emlyn, principal of The Elms school at Woodleigh Common.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyUnmarried Crackenthorpe daughter who keeps house for her father Luther; kind to her nephews and determined to hold the family together after the train murder<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonStranger staying at The Stagg and blackmailer<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodMr Entwhistle, the Abernethie family's long-serving solicitor from the firm of Bollard, Entwhistle, Entwhistle and Bollard.<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralLodgekeeper and legal father of Mary<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressArchaeologist in charge of the dig<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaSecretary to Mr Rafiel who accompanies him on his holiday to St Honore.<br><br>Appears in: A Caribbean MysteryPale, frightened housekeeper-cook serving with her husband Thomas on Indian Island.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneCousin of Hattie Stubbs, whom he has not seen since her convent-school days.<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyAttractive wife of Guy Carpenter living in Broadhinny.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadWoman married to Edward Hillingdon, staying at the Golden Palm Hotel on St Honore.<br><br>Appears in: A Caribbean MysteryMiss Evelyn Howard, forthright companion to Emily Inglethorp; fiercely protective of her friend and openly distrustful of Alfred<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesFrench cleric and epigraphist who joins the archaeological expedition at Tell Yarimjah.<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaMan who attacks Hastings in Paris<br><br>Appears in: The Big Four<b>Disambiguation:</b><br>• <a href="bword://Dr Ferguson">Dr Ferguson</a> - The family doctor for the Reynolds<br>• <a href="bword://Mr Ferguson">Mr Ferguson</a> - Communist traveller writing about ‘conditions’Wealthy widow in King’s Abbot and close friend of Roger Ackroyd.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydPretty, self-possessed niece and ward of Roger; newly engaged to Ralph Paton and heiress to a legacy that gives her a firm alibi on the night of the murder<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydOld friend of actor Claude Darrell who is drawn into the Big Four affair.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourRespectable sister who supplies Ursula Bourne a reference and later reveals the parlourmaid’s true background and secret marriage<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydFlatmate of Norma Restarick and Claudia Reece-Holland, working at an art gallery in Bond Street.<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlWife of Jeremy Cloade and member of the financially strained Cloade family in Warmsley Vale.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodFrançoise, elderly housekeeper at the Renauld villa; loyal to Madame Eloise and shocked by the night’s strange comings and goings<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksYoung man loosely courting Gladys Nevill and suspected in the Morley case.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeConway Jefferson's deceased son.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryYounger, dynamic brother of Sir Carmichael Clarke; outwardly devoted, he helps Poirot while professing to protect his ailing sister-in-law<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersBrutish estranged husband of Alice Ascher; a drunkard who extorts money from her and draws early police suspicion after her murder<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersCook at Rutherford Hall.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonWorks at the fishmonger in St Mary Mead and is known for chatting with the local girls.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeLocal Devon boatman who ferries provisions and the ten guests to Indian Island; notes the odd secrecy of the hosts but leaves before the trap is sprung<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneClose friend and neighbour of Nick Buckley at End House.<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HouseConvict at Dartmoor in Pricetown who escapes.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryGerman maid at Hunter’s Close for the Weatherby’s<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadGabriel Stonor, discreet English secretary to Paul Renauld; travelled with him from South America and shields details of Renauld’s past<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksTalkative friend of Caroline Sheppard in King’s Abbot; eagerly trades village news, spreading every whisper about Mrs Ferrars and Roger Ackroyd<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydAmerican tourist<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunHusband of Margaret and father of Celia<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberGrizzled World War I general who sent his wife’s lover Arthur Richmond on a fatal mission; lives with silent regret and dreads the “letter” that summons him<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneFriend of Carlotta<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesCheerful, athletic young secretary who dines at Fernly, knows the household routines and stands to gain a modest legacy in Ackroyd’s will<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydPhysician and friend of Lady Frances Derwent.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansNephew of Richard Abernethie, a solicitor in a stockbroker's office and one of the Abernethie heirs.<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralMild-mannered barber of Doncaster.<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersMember of Parliament and Simeon’s son<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasHonourable George Lomax of the Foreign Office and host at Wyvern Abbey.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryJunior partner in his father’s firm; brings Poirot the sixteen‑year‑old files and accompanies Carla Lemarchant when she commissions the new inquiry<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsCurrent owner of Nasse House and married to Hattie<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollySister of Henry Morley, living with him at their flat above the dental practice in Queen Charlotte Street.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeArtist and nephew of Mr Paynter, heir to his uncle's fortune.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourYoung Foreign Office man and guest at the Chimneys house party.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysterySchool master in love with Elaine.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of Rye10 year old girl living across from 19 Wilbraham Crescent who has a broken leg<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksLord Edgware's daughter from his first marriage.<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesDr Theodore Gerard, French psychiatrist travelling with the Boynton party in the Middle East.<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathAlistair Blunt’s first wife<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeWife of Dr John Christow, plain and anxious, and mother of their two children.<br><br>Appears in: The HollowInjured pilot staying with his sister Joanna in Lymstock.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerCora’s companion and house keeper<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralHusband of Gwenda Halliday Reed and a cousin of Joan West.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderDoctor in Hassaneih and friend of Poirot’s<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaYoung American chess champion who vanishes after becoming involved in the Big Four case.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourCarrie Louise's adopted daughter, married to Wally.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsDaughter of Mrs Boynton, imaginative and mentally fragile, often called Jinny.<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathSwaggering Paris Sûreté detective who relies on footprints and cigarettes; clashes with Poirot’s “little grey cells” while hunting the Renauld killer<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksItalian who worked at the Blitz Hotel, he's a criminal.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysYoung maid at the Stag Inn in Warmsley Vale.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodYoung maid in the Clements’ household; skittish and talkative, she notices movements around the study on the evening Protheroe is shot<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageMaid at Yewtree Lodge and Miss Marple's former student.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeSecretary and receptionist at Dr Henry Morley's dental practice in Queen Charlotte Street.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeHousekeeper at the vicarage in Marchbolt and former parlourmaid at Tudor Cottage.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansPoirot’s PI and also Rufus Van Aldin’s informant in The Mystery of the Blue Train<br><br>Appears in: After The Funeral, Elephants Can Remember, The Mystery Of The Blue Train & The Third GirlVillage witch and helper at the party<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyWealthy husband of Rosaleen Cloade and brother of David Hunter’s mother.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodFirst wife of Andrew Restarick and mother of Norma Restarick.<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlDr Grainger, Emily Arundell's physician in Market Basing and senior partner to Rex Donaldson.<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessInvestigating officer<br><br>Appears in: The HollowHusband of Susan Banks and a schoolmaster by profession.<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralGentle Swedish missionary nurse from a Christian order; once Daisy Armstrong’s devoted nursemaid and deeply marked by the tragedy in the household<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressYoung German au pair employed by the McNaughton family in Crowdean.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksGriselda Clement, lively much younger wife of the vicar; frank about village gossip and fiercely loyal despite appearing frivolous<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageButler at The Hollow and one of the domestic staff serving the Angkatell household.<br><br>Appears in: The HollowIntense Italian archaeologist traveling under government orders; guards a briefcase of political papers and views fellow passengers with suspicion<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileRunning in politics, married to Eve<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadSecretary to Sir Eustace.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitNew Zealand-raised bride who purchases a house in England.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderInspector Hale, original police officer on the Alderbury case; gathered statements sixteen years earlier that Poirot re-examines in his “five little pigs” inquiry<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsWife of the missing scientist John Halliday, who seeks help in tracing him.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourArranges the interview between Poirot and John Ingles<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourSmall, precise solicitor handling Roger Ackroyd’s affairs and Mrs Ferrars’ will; summoned to Fernly to open the safe and outline the legacies<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydLoyal cook-housemaid at Little Paddocks, Hungarian refugee who mistrusts strangers yet becomes a witness to the staged holdup<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedHelper at the party<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyElderly invalid to whom Katherine Grey was companion; leaves her a fortune, enabling the Riviera journey where the Blue Train mystery begins<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainHarold Crackenthorpe, smooth solicitor son of Luther; keeps a cautious eye on the inheritance and resents interruptions to Rutherford Hall’s routine<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonAnother of Simeon’s sons who has recently returned from abroad<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasA friend of John Eardsley accused of assisting him with the theft of the diamonds reported as missing in action.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitAgent of the British Intelligence Service<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourWealthy young wife of Sir George Stubbs and cousin of Etienne de Sousa.<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyExamining magistrate and Giraud’s assistant<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksAmerican journalist associated with the Seven Dials group.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryLocal woman and enthusiastic admirer of Marina Gregg.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideBig game hunter, friend of Roger Ackroyd in love with Flora<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydEarnest American secretary and translator to Ratchett; son of the district attorney involved in the Armstrong case and protective of Sonia’s memory<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressOne of the young guests at the Cootes' house party at Chimneys.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryWidowed sister-in-law to Richard Abernethie<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralGwenda Reed’s stepmother from her childhood memories at Hillside.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderMr MacKenzie’s wife, a resident at Pinewood Private Sanatorium.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeAlistair Blunt’s first wife<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeCurate Hawes' sister.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageGerman scientist.<br><br>Appears in: Destination UnknownResident at 20 Wilbraham Crescent with her many cats<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksAn assistant to Ariadne Oliver<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourFrench gentleman whom Hilary Craven meets on the train from Casablanca to Fez.<br><br>Appears in: Destination UnknownA sculptor having an affair with John Christow<br><br>Appears in: The HollowSir Henry Angkatell, owner of The Hollow and husband of Lucy Angkatell.<br><br>Appears in: The HollowHusband of Sylvia Bassington-ffrench, father of Thomas, and a justice of the peace.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansSteward on the Paris-to-Croydon flight on which Madame Giselle is found dead.<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsHercule Poirot’s dentist at 58 Queen Charlotte Street.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My Shoe"Poirot was an extraordinary-looking little man. He was hardly more than five feet four inches, but carried himself with great dignity. His head was exactly the shape of an egg, and he always perched it a little on one side. His moustache was very stiff and military. The neatness of his attire was almost incredible; I believe a speck of dust would have caused him more pain than a bullet wound."American at Chimney's to study the art there.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysAlso known as Egg and love interest of Sir Charles<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyGerman inventor invited to Wyvern Abbey to discuss his aeronautical formula with British officials.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryColonel Easterbrook’s daughter, staying at the Royal Spa Hotel.<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedA deserted wife and bereaved mother contemplating suicide.<br><br>Appears in: Destination UnknownWife of David Lee and daughter-in-law of Simeon Lee at Gorston Hall.<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasStout, capable German ladies’ maid to Princess Dragomiroff; formerly the Armstrong family cook and still loyal to the memory of their home<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressPoirot’s solicitor<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourHeadteacher and founder of Meadowbank<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsChic society girl and jewel thief; Linnet’s friend and cousin of Tim Allerton who sends him to Egypt carrying pearls to fence<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileAcquaintance of the Ravenscrofts<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberLively daughter of Lady Tamplin; part of the Riviera set Katherine Grey joins, flitting between dances and gossip at the Hotel du Cap<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainFriend of the Horbury’s and passenger on the plane where the murder was committed<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsSir Horace Blatt, wealthy owner of the hotel on Smugglers' Island.<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunSydney Horbury, valet to Simeon Lee at Gorston Hall.<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasGardener employed by Mrs Laura Welman at Hunterbury.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressPolitical activist and boyfriend of Jane<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeMrs Hubbard, Miss Lemon's widowed sister and warden of the Hickory Road student hostel.<br><br>Appears in: Hickory Dickory DockUncle of Cyril, a man Vera Claythorne once hoped to marry.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneHusband of Pamela McRae.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryInvestigating officer.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysInspector Dermot Craddock of Scotland Yard; methodical and courteous, he works with Miss Marple to untangle identities after the advertised “murder” occurs<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedScotland Yard detective.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideDevon police inspector who assists Sir Thomas Legge in reconstructing the Indian Island case after the fact, poring over the guests’ pasts and alibis<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneScotland Yard detective investigating the death of the unknown woman found at Mill House.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitPolice inspector who leads the investigation into the murder of Joseph Trevelyan at Exhampton.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryDetective Inspector of the CID who handles the deaths at the Fortescue home.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeNeighbour of Emily Arundell, sister of Julia<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessImpulsive son of Paul and Eloise; engaged to Marthe Daubreuil after a brief infatuation with dancer Bella, his movements the night of the murder draw suspicion<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksLocal businessman in Devon, formerly a law clerk and later owner of Daffodil Coaches.<br><br>Appears in: Sleeping MurderBella’s Greek husband working in Smyrna<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessNeighbour to Claudia and lived below Louise<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlPassionate, impulsive friend of Linnet Ridgeway; persuaded Linnet to hire Simon Doyle, then followed the couple to Egypt after losing her fiancé to her heiress friend<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileAbe Ryland’s footman<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourChemist from New Zealand who gives evidence at Elinor Carlisle's trial.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressMrs McGinty’s lodger and accused of her murder<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadInnocent man sent to prison for life and who later died there.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneAnthony's Canadian friend from whom he accepts the memoirs.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysVillage doctor of King’s Abbot and narrator; lives with his sister Caroline beside Poirot’s cottage and is summoned when Roger Ackroyd is found dead<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydYoung man who helped Lucy on a train journey.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonHusband of Edith Waterhouse and one of the residents of 18 Wilbraham Crescent.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksA missing woman who held important documents.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryHairdresser and passenger on the plane where the murder was committed<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsAmateur detective, friend of the Bantry’s.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryDaughter of Julia Olivera and one of the patients at Henry Morley's dental practice.<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeAmerican actress, married to Lord Edgware but separated<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesHousekeeper for the Upwards<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadEnglish tourist.<br><br>Appears in: Destination UnknownTeacher at Woodleigh Common School and friend of Judith Butler.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyMarina Gregg's husband, a film director.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideArchaeologist and son of Armand Dupont, passenger on the plane where the murder was committed<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsFamily friend of the Boynton’s<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathFormer employer of Mr and Mrs Rogers.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneWife of Percival Fortescue, known in the family as Mrs Val.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeSimon Lees daughter – deceased<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasStudent at Meadowbank, Joan Sutcliffe’s daughter and Niece of Bob Rawlinson. Avid tennis player and best friends with Julia<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsCanon Jeremy Prescott, holidaymaker on St Honoré who travels with his sister Joan Prescott.<br><br>Appears in: A Caribbean MysterySolicitor and older brother of George Cloade, married to Frances<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodVillage solicitor who lives with his wife in a nearby house called By the Way.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyYoung English solicitor from Carmichael & Company, traveling incognito to watch over Linnet and Simon’s interests and quietly observe the passengers<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileJeweller and dealer in works of art in Bond Street.<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HouseYoung man about town with an expensive lifestyle and a place in the Chimneys circle.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryBob Rawlinson’s sister and mother to Jennifer, student at Meadowbank<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsPretty and compassionate sister of Jerry Burton, who accompanies him to Lymstock.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerHusband of Mrs McGinty's niece and one of the locals connected with the Broadhinny inquiry.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadTall British army officer returning from India; close friend of Colonel Armstrong from the war and quietly attached to the self-possessed Mary Debenham<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressNew footman at Chimneys, sent there by Mr Mosgorovsky as Alfred's replacement.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryJohn Cavendish, eldest stepson of Emily Inglethorp; calm country gentleman trying to keep peace at Styles after his mother’s impulsive remarriage<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesDoctor researching the treatment of Ridgeway’s disease and husband of Gerda Christow.<br><br>Appears in: The HollowThe son of a South African gold magnate Sir Laurence who is disowned after being accused of theft.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitChemist and experimental doctor working on a treatment for the incurable Ridgeway's disease.<br><br>Appears in: CurtainScientist whose disappearance is one of the international cases connected with the Big Four.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourRetired civil servant and neighbour of Mr Paynter at the Elmers Dale estate.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourDisciplined butler at Fernly Park; once dismissed from another post for reading notes in a tray, attentive to movements in the study on the night of the murder<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydBusinessman and millionaire whose affairs draw Alan Carstairs into the mystery.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansDoctor and psychiatrist, a close friend of Hercule Poirot.<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlHusband of Maureen Summerhayes and friend of Superintendent Spence in Broadhinny.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadFarming partner of Rowley Cloade.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodHousemaid at the institute.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsMan connected with the Granite Bungalow case on Dartmoor.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourTheatrical agent and friend of Hercule Poirot.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The Links, The Big Four, The Mystery Of The Blue TrainColleague of Dr Leidner working at the dig, married to Marie<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaResident at 61 Wilbraham Crescent and a builder<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksDancer at the Majestic Hotel.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryBoastful child at the Hallowe’en party in Woodleigh Common.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyAriadne’s friend whom she stay with and mother of Miranda<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyCaptain Hasting’s daughter and lab assistant to Dr Franklin<br><br>Appears in: CurtainAlistair Blunt’s sister-in-law (of his first wife)<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeNeighbour of Emily Arundell, sister of Isabel<br><br>Appears in: Dumb WitnessStudent at Meadowbank, Mrs Upjohn’s daughter. Best friends with Jennifer<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsFriend of Lettice Protheroe who hosts a tennis party.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsJane Fin's millionaire cousin.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryWidow of Lionel Cloade and a spiritualist among the Cloade relations in Warmsley Vale.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodQuiet former lady’s companion who unexpectedly inherits a fortune; takes the Blue Train to the Riviera, befriends Ruth Kettering, and provides Poirot a clear-eyed witness<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainOwner of Cavendish Secretarial Bureau and sister of Valerie Bland.<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksArlena’s current husband, father of Linda<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunMember of United States secret service<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourPlasterer’s wife<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadRenowned thief who has escaped from France and is a master of disguise. He stole the Koh-i-Noor diamond from London and is wanted in three countries.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysRace car driver associated with Lady Sedgwick and admired by her daughter Elvira.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelWife of Harold Crackenthorpe and daughter of an impoverished earl.<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonLord Caterham's daughter and friend of Virginia.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of Chimneys, The Seven Dials MysteryDaughter of Lord Marchington and close friend of Bobby Jones.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansWife of Sir Oswald Coote and hostess of the Chimneys house party.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryFriend of Miss Marple staying at Bertram's Hotel and a useful source of gossip and background information.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelLancelot 'Lance' Fortescue, younger son of Rex Fortescue and long estranged from his father.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeButler<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralVillage baker in Broadhinny<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadAdoptive mother of Robin Upward.<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadLavinia Glynne, widowed sister of Anthea and Clotilde Bradbury-Scott, living at the Old Manor House in Jocelyn St Mary.<br><br>Appears in: NemesisLawrence Cavendish, younger stepson of Emily Inglethorp; sensitive, literary and tense after her death, he hides his own movements on the fatal night<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesArtist who uses the shed in the vicarage garden as his studio.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageSheila Webb’s aunt<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksMan who falls on the tracks at Hyde Park Tube station.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitMysterious jewel thief known as “Le Marquis,” suspected of stalking the Heart of Fire rubies and shadowing Ruth Kettering on the Blue Train<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainResident at The Stagg Inn<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodDr Ferguson’s dispenser<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartySecond step-son of Mrs Boynton<br><br>Appears in: Appointment With DeathSupposed brother-in-law of Alex Pritchard and husband of Amelia Cayman.<br><br>Appears in: Why Didn't They Ask EvansMedical student at the hostel<br><br>Appears in: Hickory Dickory DockReverend Leonard Clement, conscientious vicar of St Mary Mead and narrator; discovers Protheroe’s body in his study and wrestles with moral dilemmas<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageYoung maid at the Ville Gernervive and Denise’s sister<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksBrother of Joyce Reynolds.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartySkilled forger with ties to events at Woodleigh Common.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyVillage youth whose romantic entanglements draw brief police attention.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageMiss Letitia Blacklock, apparent owner of Little Paddocks; calm, practical hostess caught at the center of the mysterious advertised “murder” party<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedDeceased, married to a committed patient and once in love with Laura Welman<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressCarrie Louise's third husband, head of the institute.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsChinese leader and mastermind<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourFeatures in the news article in the Sunday Comet about female killers<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadLively daughter of Mrs Marbury, Cust’s landlady in London; chats with the lodger and unwittingly notices his mysterious parcel of stockings<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersKenneth’s daughter by his first wife<br><br>Appears in: Evil Under The SunBrilliantly rich young heiress, daughter of Melhuish Ridgeway and wife of Simon Doyle.<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileDoctor and younger brother of George Cloade, married to Katherine<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodWealthy widow who employed Michael Garfield to design her garden.<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyHollywood actress, Jason Rudd's former wife.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideStepsister of Gerald Wade who lives at Deane Priory with Mrs Coker.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryMarquess of Caterham, owner of Chimneys and father of Bundle, Dulcie and Daisy.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of Chimneys, The Seven Dials MysteryEnglish peer married to actress Jane Wilkinson.<br><br>Appears in: Lord Edgware DiesAnne's employer, owner of the Daily Budget.<br><br>Appears in: The Man In The Brown SuitLord of the manor – obnoxious millionaire engaged to Bridget.<br><br>Appears in: Murder is EasyWidow and guest of Mr Shaitana – Bridge player<br><br>Appears in: Cards On The TableFormer patient whose case weighs on Dr Armstrong’s conscience.<br><br>Appears in: And Then There Were NoneLoyal French lady’s maid to Linnet Doyle; fearful of losing her position after the marriage and uneasy amid the tensions on the Karnak<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileAmerican married to Dr Leidner her second husband<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaFrench nursemaid in the Armstrong household.<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressItalian wife of Richard Amory<br><br>Appears in: Black CoffeeCommissary of Police at Merlinville-sur-Mer; courteous and methodical, he first calls Poirot into the Renauld affair and balances tact with official duty<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksSir Henry’s wife and mistress of The Hollow<br><br>Appears in: The HollowBrilliant young professional housekeeper sent by Miss Marple to Rutherford Hall; efficient, unflappable, and central to uncovering the body hidden on the estate<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonGerman-speaking Austrian physician with a clinic on the Rhine; quarrels with Ferguson and tends the honeymoon party after the shooting on board<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileRecently returned to England from India where he worked in the police. He meets Miss Pinkerton on the train to London.<br><br>Appears in: Murder is EasyLuther Crackenthorpe, irascible patriarch of Rutherford Hall; sits in his train-carriage dining room guarding the family fortune and goading his grasping sons<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonMarried to Major Horton, she had been invalided for some time before dying.<br><br>Appears in: Murder is EasyMarried to Alfred<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasRecently returned Wren and engaged to Rowley Cloade.<br><br>Appears in: Taken At The FloodHospital nurse<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourDental patient<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeHead gardener at Chimneys, a formidable and imposing Scotsman who rules his domain with authority.<br><br>Appears in: The Seven Dials MysteryPaul Renauld's neighbour in Merlinville and the mother of Marthe Daubreuil.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksFrench moneylender who travels by air under the name Madame Giselle.<br><br>Appears in: Death In The CloudsYoung wife of George<br><br>Appears in: Hercule Poirot’s ChristmasNick’s cousin who comes to visit<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HousePoliceman<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaA retired military man who enjoys sports and best friend of Cpt. Trevelyn.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryRetired military major, guest at the Golden Palm.<br><br>Appears in: A Caribbean MysteryA well-known gentleman in the village and heartthrob.<br><br>Appears in: Endless NightSergeant Marchaud of the local gendarmerie; takes statements in Merlinville and reports movements of suspects on the night of Renauld’s death<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksWife of Reverend Babbington and one of the guests at Sir Charles Cartwright's cocktail party.<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyWife of Alistair and mother of Celia. She has a twin sister<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberPreviously an actress, traveling on board of the Lusitania with Jane Finn.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret AdversaryWife of Joseph<br><br>Appears in: Murder In MesopotamiaWealthy and exclusive American socialite. Cousin of Cornelia<br><br>Appears in: Death On The NileHollywood actress who buys a house near Miss Marple.<br><br>Appears in: The Mirror Crack'd from Side to SideLocal teenager who takes part in the fete murder game at Nasse House.<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyBeautiful daughter of Madame Daubreuil and fiancée of Jack Renauld.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder On The LinksAbe Ryland’s stenographer<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourHigh profile politician/banker<br><br>Appears in: One, Two, Buckle My ShoeUnknown Frenchwoman later identified as “Martine,” the corpse hurled from the passing train; her identity links the Crackenthorpes to the murder plot<br><br>Appears in: 4.50 From PaddingtonMary Hill, maid at the vicarage in St Mary Mead at the time of Colonel Protheroe's murder.<br><br>Appears in: The Murder at the VicarageDolly Bantry, wife of Colonel Arthur Bantry and owner of Gossington Hall in St Mary Mead.<br><br>Appears in: The Body in the LibraryMary Cavendish, cool, independent wife of John; enjoys her garden and the companionship of Dr Bauerstein, arousing Poirot’s curiosity during the inquiry<br><br>Appears in: The Mysterious Affair At StylesCalm, self-contained English governess traveling from Baghdad; once nanny to Daisy Armstrong, she hides deep loyalties beneath her controlled exterior<br><br>Appears in: Murder On The Orient ExpressHousekeeper at Yewtree Lodge, noted for being efficient, detached and rather ironic.<br><br>Appears in: A Pocket Full of RyeYoung niece who helps her Aunt Alice in the Andover shop.<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersMrs Welman’s young protégé who grew up at the lodge near Hunterbury.<br><br>Appears in: Sad CypressEgg’s mother and guest at Sir Charles’ party<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyAndrew’s young second wife and stepmother to Norma<br><br>Appears in: The Third GirlBella ad Jacob’s daughter<br><br>Appears in: Dumb Witnessthe nursemaid to the Ravenscrofts<br><br>Appears in: Elephants Can RememberWife of Timothy – Richard Abernethie’s brother<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralYoung lady who worked at Breather and Scuttle and believes in James Bentley’s innocence<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadRuns the guest house in the village<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadResident of 63 Wilbraham Crescent, Agnus’ wife<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksPoirot’s solicitor<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourPoliceman involved in the Jonathan Whalley case.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourSerious elder sister of Betty Barnard and a steady presence in her family.<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersEmily Barton’s niece, a troubled young girl.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerCounty Chief Constable who confers with Inspector Raglan, backs the official line yet pragmatically invites Poirot’s aid when the case grows tangled<br><br>Appears in: The Murder Of Roger AckroydElderly boatman and grandfather of Marlene Tucker.<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyRetired country gentleman and amateur herbalist living near Alderbury; once kept the coniine that was taken, carries guilt for his part in the tragedy<br><br>Appears in: Five Little PigsActress and person who identifies the body as her estranged husband<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksFormer member of the secret service.<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourMichael Rafiel, son of the late Jason Rafiel.<br><br>Appears in: NemesisGarber and landscaper<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyPrince Michael Obolovitch of Herzoslovakia, a claimant to the restored throne who stays at Chimneys.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysInvestigating narrator who marries Ellie the heiress.<br><br>Appears in: Endless NightWealthy adventurer and pilot who goes missing<br><br>Appears in: Peril At End HouseRosamund’s husband<br><br>Appears in: After The FuneralEmployee at the theatre where Ariadne Oliver’s novel is being turned into a play<br><br>Appears in: Mrs McGinty’s DeadArchitect<br><br>Appears in: Dead Man’s FollyIrish doorman at Bertram's Hotel.<br><br>Appears in: At Bertram's HotelMrs Templeton’s son from a previous marriage<br><br>Appears in: The Big FourLady Lucy’s young cousin who works at a dress makers<br><br>Appears in: The HollowWidowed daughter of Eric Gulbrandsen and Carrie Louise Serrocold, living at Stonygates.<br><br>Appears in: They Do It with MirrorsBlind teacher living at 19 Wilbraham Crescent. Teaches at local school for the blind (Sheila’s Webb’s estranged mother)<br><br>Appears in: The ClocksBarmaid at the Ginger Cat who worked alongside Betty Barnard; provides Poirot details of Betty’s habits and admirers<br><br>Appears in: The ABC MurdersSpinster servant of Sir Charles<br><br>Appears in: Three Act TragedyDaughter to Judith and friend of Joyce Reynolds<br><br>Appears in: Hallowe’en PartyFamous dancer once involved with Derek Kettering; proud of her beauty and quick temper, questioned by Poirot about threats to Ruth’s jewels<br><br>Appears in: The Mystery Of The Blue TrainThe invalid lady who keeps her eyes and ears open, resident of Sittaford who has her nephew Ronald Garfield to stay.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryNurse to the invalid Robert Gardner in The Sittaford Mystery.<br><br>Appears in: The Sittaford MysteryThe governess to Dulcie and Daisy, Lord Caterhams two young daughters.<br><br>Appears in: The Secret Of ChimneysFormer clerk to Richard Symmington who later works at the property agent's office in Lymstock.<br><br>Appears in: The Moving FingerForthright retired schoolteacher who lives with Amy Murgatroyd; quick-witted and protective when the lights go out at Little Paddocks<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedMatron at Meadowbank<br><br>Appears in: Cat Among The PigeonsJane Marple, observant spinster from St Mary Mead; invited by the Easterbrooks and quietly pieces together the truth behind the advertised murder<br><br>Appears in: A Murder is AnnouncedNew secretary traveling with Sir Eustace from Cape Town.<